element.name: Dodder - St. Anne's by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

long-description.p: One of a series of caches along the Dodder River – the paths linking these caches is wheelchair and buggy/pram passable, unless otherwise stated. All the caches in this series are also accessible to the wheelchair user, unless otherwise stated.

This one is a micro-cache (bring a pen/pencil to sign the log!) hidden near St. Anne’s – a former secondary school and convent. The school is now closed and most of the lands have been sold for development – apartments and houses. The cache is accessible by, and from, wheelchair – car park is at N 53 18.677 W 006 14.836. You could also park at N 53 18.475 W 006 15.338 and take in the “Dodder – Dropping Well” cache and the “Dodder – Dartry Park” cache.
